  <section class="bg-[#0d1f2b] py-28">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">

      <div class="text-center mb-14">
        <p class="text-evium-green text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase mb-4">Fleet Charging FAQ</p>
        <h2 class="text-white font-black text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight">
          Answers for Fleet Managers.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-0 border border-white/8">

        <details class="group border-b border-white/8">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-8 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-lg pr-8">What size fleet depot can Evium handle?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-evium-green/40 flex items-center justify-center text-evium-green group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-8 pb-8">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-base leading-relaxed">
              Evium scales from small municipal fleets of 10–20 vehicles up to large commercial depots with 200+ vehicles and multi-megawatt charging loads. Our site assessment process accounts for current fleet size, projected EV adoption timeline, and available electrical capacity — and designs an infrastructure plan that fits all three.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border-b border-white/8">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-8 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-lg pr-8">How does load management actually work?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-evium-green/40 flex items-center justify-center text-evium-green group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-8 pb-8">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-base leading-relaxed">
              Our OCPP 1.6+ platform uses real-time demand data to dynamically distribute available electrical capacity across all active chargers. When grid demand rises or a circuit approaches its limit, the system automatically throttles lower-priority sessions and boosts higher-priority ones — without interrupting charging. Open ADR 2.0b integration allows the system to respond to utility demand response signals, which can also generate revenue or credits for your operation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border-b border-white/8">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-8 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-lg pr-8">What does ongoing maintenance look like?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-evium-green/40 flex items-center justify-center text-evium-green group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-8 pb-8">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-base leading-relaxed">
              Evium's platform monitors all chargers 24/7 with automated fault detection. Most software-level issues are resolved remotely via OTA firmware updates or remote session management without requiring a site visit. For hardware faults, Evium dispatches a certified technician. Under our operations agreements, we also conduct scheduled preventive maintenance visits to inspect connectors, check electrical connections, and update firmware — before problems affect uptime.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border-b border-white/8">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-8 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-lg pr-8">When should a fleet use L2 vs. DC fast charging?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-evium-green/40 flex items-center justify-center text-evium-green group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-8 pb-8">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-base leading-relaxed">
              Level 2 (7–19 kW) is the right choice for vehicles that sit overnight or for extended periods — it's lower cost per port, gentler on batteries, and sufficient for most light and medium-duty EVs. DC fast charging (60–240 kW) is for vehicles that need a meaningful charge in under an hour — quick-turn delivery vehicles, transit buses on layover, or emergency vehicles that must return to service rapidly. Most depot designs use both: L2 as the primary backbone with a small number of DCFC stalls for peak demand.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border-b border-white/8">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-8 cursor-pointer list-none select-none">
            <span class="text-white font-semibold text-lg pr-8">Does Evium handle permits and utility coordination?</span>
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-evium-green/40 flex items-center justify-center text-evium-green group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-8 pb-8">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-base leading-relaxed">
              Yes — completely. Evium manages the full permitting process including electrical, building, and ADA permits where required. We also handle all utility company coordination: interconnection applications, service upgrades, demand response enrollment, and rebate applications. This is often the most time-consuming and technically complex part of a depot build, and it's entirely off your plate.
